    Inspect long/wide/imputed data

    inspectData.Rd

    Inspect long/wide/imputed data

    inspectData(
  data,
  exposure,
  exposure_time_pts,
  outcome,
  ti_confounders,
  tv_confounders,
  epochs = NULL,
  hi_lo_cut = NULL,
  reference = NULL,
  comparison = NULL,
  home_dir = NA,
  verbose = TRUE,
  save.out = TRUE
)

    Arguments

    data

    data in wide format as: a data frame, list of imputed data frames, or mids object

    exposure

    name of exposure variable

    exposure_time_pts

    list of integers at which weights will be created/assessed that correspond to time points when exposure was measured

    outcome

    name of outcome variable with ".timepoint" suffix

    ti_confounders

    list of time invariant confounders

    tv_confounders

    list of time-varying confounders with ".timepoint" suffix (time-varying exposure variables requires to be listed here)

    epochs

    (optional) data frame of exposure epoch labels and values

    hi_lo_cut

    (optional) list of two numbers indicating quantile values that reflect high and low values, respectively, for continuous exposure (default is median split)

    reference

    (optional) list of one or more strings of "-"-separated "l" and "h" values indicative of a reference exposure history to which to compare comparison, required if comparison is specified

    comparison

    (optional) list of one or more strings of "-"-separated "l" and "h" values indicative of comparison history/histories to compare to reference, required if reference is specified

    home_dir

    (optional) path to home directory (required if save.out = TRUE)

    verbose

    (optional) TRUE or FALSE indicator for user output (default is TRUE)

    save.out

    (optional) TRUE or FALSE indicator to save output and intermediary output locally (default is TRUE)

    Value

    none

    Examples

    test <- data.frame(ID = 1:50,
                   A.1 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   A.2 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   A.3 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   B.1 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   B.2 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   B.3 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   C = rnorm(n = 50),
                   D.3 = rnorm(n = 50))
test[, c("A.1", "A.2", "A.3")] <- lapply(test[, c("A.1", "A.2", "A.3")], as.numeric)

inspectData(data = test,
            exposure = "A",
            exposure_time_pts = c(1, 2, 3),
            outcome = "D.3",
            tv_confounders = c("A.1", "A.2", "A.3"),
            ti_confounders = "C",
            save.out = FALSE)
